{
  "stem": "13690.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "In other words, there were people producing those papers from the Germans, obtaining them from the Germans' authority, from the county clerk at the county offices, and giving out papers to the people to run away.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, they were regular--",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Regular permits to move into to a different section, a different part of Poland.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We obtained those papers for the entire family-- father, mother, and three of us-- and we had to run away.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was not a question that we could just sit in a car, we had to order a horse and buggy.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we went with two horses, with a Gentile, and they took us to another town.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "30 Kilometers to a town being called Pilica, P-I-L-I-C-A.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We did not have to hide.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were just-- this town was already, so to say, after the liquidation of the ghetto, so to say, Judenrein-- it was clean of Jews.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we were just walking around.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We had permission to stay there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Permission?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes, we have permission to stay there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Absolutely.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That's correct.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were staying there a few weeks, and then we moved back to Zarki after this town was practically also liquidated.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There were 30 Jews left.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "30 Jews were left behind, just the few Jews which were actually the authorities, so to say.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And some were left behind also to clean up the mess that they created.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were hundreds of people were killed, and quite a disorder in the whole town.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The liquidation of the ghetto, which I stated, was the last day of the holiday of Sukkoth, the Tabernacle, it was that they-- to the actual liquidation of the ghetto, the Germans could not the round up more than 700 people.",
      "word_count": 41
    }
  ],
